      "strongs_list": "[{\"strong\": \"G2643\", \"count\": 4}]",
      "description": "Reconciliation is the restoration of broken relationship — the movement from alienation and hostility back to genuine peace and communion. The Greek vocabulary is specific: the exchange of enmity for friendship, the resolution of the thing that stood between two parties. In the New Testament, reconciliation is the great theological word for what God has done in Christ: the relationship between God and humanity, broken by sin, is restored through the cross. Human reconciliation — between individuals, between peoples — is both modelled on and enabled by this divine act.",
